This game is full of hilarious pirate action and exciting environments to discover! And then you get this calm, heavenly piece of music, that basically says to you: "Hold on, you've already made it this far, and you'll reach your goal soon! Keep searching around in these wonderful, shimmering ice caves, because in the end, you'll meet with a good old seal friend! He will be there for you to help you progress through his beautiful home!"

It is so heart-warming!

snippet.textDisplay: I just realized DKC2 has 2 kinds of water stages.  The first type being the rather grim and tense ship hold type levels while the more soothing atmosphere type levels take place in these crystal caverns made of ice.  What's quite ironic is the calmer ice cave themed water levels come later in the game in the sixth world and as such are not surprisingly harder then the more intense atmosphere ones in the ship holds.  Well there is Black Ice Battle in the secret world 8 which doesn't have water in it.  Unless of course you consider it a water stage by technicality due to it being all frozen.
